title: S.J. boys: Overtime strike lifts Cherokee soccer
text:
More coverage: Southeastern Pa. high school sports Sean Donnelly scored in the second half to give Lenape a 1-0 win over visiting Bishop Eustace.
J.T. Morgan and Drew Ruble each scored for Shawnee in a 2-0 defeat of visiting Cherry Hill West. 
Burlington County. Doran Keys scored the winner for Maple Shade in a 4-3 overtime win at Florence. Keys also scored earlier in the match. 
Mat Shaddow scored two goals in the second half, and Holy Cross rallied to beat host Trenton Catholic, 2-1. 
Colonial. Oumar Sylla scored a hat trick in the first half, as Lindenwold defeated host Haddon Township, 4-3. 
Chase Conover, Dominic DeGeorge, and Nick Steigerwald each scored to lead host Gateway past Woodbury, 3-2.
